<title>ITALY: Italy's Ciampi sees further fall in inflation.</title>
<headline>Italy's Ciampi sees further fall in inflation.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-03-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Treasury Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi said he expected Italian inflation to fall again in the coming months after the dip in prices registered in February.</p>
<p>Inflation fell to 2.4 percent year-on-year last month from 2.6 percent in January.</p>
<p>&quot;The February data confirms the falling trend for inflation which should continue to decline,&quot; Ciampi told reporters.</p>
